result.name: Oyster King

reviews.text: Nice and decent steak and oyster restaurant in Tai Po. Airy place with simple but comfortable seating. Good menu selection not to mention their oyster selection. We had lunch the other day where you have a choice of soups for starter, selection of main courses with coffee or tea for a set price depending what main course you opt for. Overall a very decent place to go in Tai Po. Recommended.
Grilled Pork Chop is good. Nice service. Recommended for lunch.
Delicious foods cooking with heart👍👍.
Good value, highly recommended for lunch.  It’s name has been changed to Oyster King, but actually it is from the same team as Jingle’s days.

result.name: Eightland Gardens

reviews.text: One of the oldest residential site right at the centre of Tai Po. You can have free shuttle buses to the Tai Po Train station. It is also a 5 mins walk to the Tai Po terminus where you can find buses to other urban areas in Hong Kong Island and Kowloon. There are also many good restaurants nearby.
very nice place  👍
